obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47517)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47517&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prisoners (Attendance in`
  line `Courts) Act, 1955.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st January, 1956, vide notification No. S.R.O. 3447, dated 8th November, 1955, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3.`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47518)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-11-56).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47518&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) "confinement in a prison"—references to confinement in a prison, by whatever form of words,`
  line `include references to confinement or detention in a prison under any law providing for preventive`
  line detention;
  line
  line `(b) "prison" includes—`
  line
  line `(i) any place which has been declared by the State Government, by general or special order,`
  line `to be a subsidiary jail; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any reformatory, Borstal institution or other institution of a like nature;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47519)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of courts to require appearance of prisoners to give evidence or answer a charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47519&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Any civil or criminal court may, if it thinks that the evidence of any person confined in any prison is`
  line `material in any matter pending before it, make an order in the form set forth in the First Schedule,`
  line `directed to the officer in charge of the prison:`
  line
  line `Provided that no civil court shall make an order under this sub-section in respect of a person confined`
  line `in a prison situated outside the State in which the court is held.`
  line
  line `(2) Any criminal court may, if a charge of an offence against a person confined in any prison is made`
  line `or pending before it, make an order in the form set forth in the Second Schedule, directed to the officer in`
  line `charge of the prison.`
  line
  line `(3) No order made under this section by a civil court which is subordinate to a district judge shall`
  line `have effect unless it is countersigned by the district judge; and no order made under this section by a`
  line `criminal court which is inferior to the court of a magistrate of the first class shall have effect unless it is`
  line `countersigned by the district magistrate to whom that court is subordinate or within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction that court is situate.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-section (3), a court of small causes outside a presidency town or the city`
  line `of Hyderabad shall be deemed to be subordinate to the district judge within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction such court is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47520)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power of State Government to exempt certain persons from operation of section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47520&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `State Government may, having regard to the matters specified in sub-section (2), by general or special`
  line `order, direct that any person or class of persons shall not be removed from the prison in which he or they`
  line `may be confined, and thereupon so long as any such order remains in force, the provisions of section 3`
  line `shall not apply to such person or class of persons.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an order under sub-section (1), the State Government shall have regard to the`
  line `following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of the offence for which or the grounds on which the confinement has been ordered`
  line `in respect of the person or class of persons;`
  line
  line `(b) the likelihood of the disturbance of public order if the person or class of persons is allowed to`
  line `be removed from the prison;`
  line
  line `(c) the public interest, generally.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47521)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prisoners to be brought up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47521&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Upon delivery of any order made under section 3 to the officer in`
  line `charge of the prison in which the person named therein is confined, that officer shall cause him to be`
  line `taken to the court in which his attendance is required, so as to be present in the court at the time of such`
  line `order mentioned, and shall cause him to be detained in custody in or near the court until he has been`
  line `examined or until the judge or presiding officer of the court authorises him to be taken back to the prison`
  line `in which he was confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (47522)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Officer in charge of prison when to abstain from carrying out order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47522&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Where the person in`
  line `respect of whom an order is made under section 3—`
  line
  line `(a) is, in accordance with the rules made in this behalf, declared to be unfit to be removed from`
  line `the prison where he is confined by reason of sickness or other infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(b) is under committal for trial; or`
  line
  line `(c) is under remand pending trial or pending a preliminary investigation; or`
  line
  line `(d) is in custody for a period which would expire before the expiration of the time required for`
  line `removing him under this Act and for taking him back to the prison in which he is confined,`
  line
  line `the officer in charge of the prison shall abstain from carrying out the order and shall send to the court`
  line `from which the order had been issued a statement of reasons for so abstaining:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer as aforesaid shall not so obstain where—`
  line
  line `(i) the order has been made by a criminal court; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the person named in the order is confined under committal for trial or under remand pending`
  line `trial or pending a preliminary investigation and is not declared in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf to be unfit to be removed from the prison where he is confined by reason of sickness or`
  line `other infirmity; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the place, where the evidence of the person named in the order is required, is not more than`
  line `five miles distant from the prison in which he is confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (47523)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Commissions for examination of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47523&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `In any of the following cases, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) where it appears to any civil court that the evidence of a person confined in a prison is`
  line `material in any matter pending before it and that the attendance of such person in court cannot be`
  line `secured by reason of the provisions of section 6 or of an order under section 4 or of the district judge`
  line `declining under sub-section (3) of section 3 to counter sign an order for removal; or`
  line
  line `(b) where it appears to any civil court as aforesaid that the evidence of a person confined in a`
  line `prison which is situated outside the State in which, or is more than fifty miles distant from the place at`
  line `which, such court is held is material in any such matter,`
  line
  line `the court may, if it thinks fit, issue a commission under the provisions of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the examination of the person in the prison in which he is confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (47524)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Certain provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure and the Code of Civil Procedure to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47524&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act and any rules made thereunder, the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), and the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), as the`
  line `case may be, shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the examination on commission or otherwise of`
  line `any person confined in a prison as they apply in relation to the examination on commission of any other`
  line person.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (47525)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47525&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for—`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure for obtaining the countersignature of an order made under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the authority by whom and the manner in which a declaration that a person confined in prison`
  line `is unfit to be removed therefrom, may be made;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions, including payment of costs and charges, subject to which an order made under`
  line `section 3 by a civil court may be executed;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which a process directed against any person confined in a prison issued from`
  line `any court may be served upon him;`
  line
  line `(e) the escort of persons confined in a prison to and from courts in which their attendance is`
  line `required and for their custody during the period of such attendance;`
  line
  line `(f) the amount to be allowed for the costs and charges of such escort; and`
  line
  line `(g) the guidance of officers in all other matters connected with the enforcement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (47526)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528&sectionId=47526&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00003_195532_1517807319528
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Part IX of the Prisoners Act, 1900 (3 of 1900) and the First and Second Schedules`
  line `to the said Act are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) If immediately before the commencement of this Act, there is in force in any Part B State to which`
  line `this Act extends any law corresponding to the provisions of this Act, that law shall, in so far as it relates`
  line `to matters dealt within this Act, stand repealed on such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken under any such law, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act and shall continue to have effect`
  line `accordingly, unless and until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
